<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-01-26T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-01-26T04:00:00-05:00" n="769" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d769">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002/972: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-01-26T18:00:00+09:00">January 26, 1940—6
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received January 27—2:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>54. Reference Shanghai’s despatch No. 2770, December 21, 1939,<note n="43" xml:id="d769fn43">Not printed.</note> taxation of imports
                                and exports by Swatow Rehabilitation Commission: tax on postal
                                parcels entering Swatow.</p>
                            <p>My British and French colleagues have informed me recently that they
                                are instructed to make representations to the Foreign Office if and
                                when I am similarly instructed. The Department’s instructions are
                                respectfully requested.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>